Name: Dumbbell Curl
Instructions: Hold dumbbells in each hand with palms facing forward, curl the weights up towards your shoulders while keeping your elbows close to your sides.

Name: Hammer Curl
Instructions: Hold dumbbells in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing your body), curl the weights up towards your shoulders while keeping your elbows close to your sides.

Name: Preacher Curl
Instructions: Sit on a preacher curl bench, place your upper arms against the angled pad, hold a barbell or dumbbell with an underhand grip, and curl the weight up towards your shoulders.

Name: Single Arm Cable Curl
Instructions: Stand facing a cable machine, grasp a handle with one hand, and curl the handle towards your shoulder while keeping your upper arm stationary.

Name: Seated Dumbbell Curl
Instructions: Sit on a bench at a slight incline, hold dumbbells in each hand with palms facing forward, and curl the weights up towards your shoulders while keeping your elbows close to your sides.

Name: Seated Hammer Curl
Instructions: Sit on a bench at a slight incline, hold dumbbells in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing your body), and curl the weights up towards your shoulders while keeping your elbows close to your sides.

Name: Close Grip Bench Press
Instructions: Lie on a bench and grip the barbell with hands closer together than shoulder-width apart, lower the barbell to your chest, and then press it back up, focusing on engaging your triceps.

Name: Single Arm Cable Extension
Instructions: Stand facing the cable machine, vertically extend your arm with the cable in hand. Alternatively, stand facing away the cable with a slight lounge, extend your arm with the cable in hand over your head and away from the machine.

Name: Cable Pushdown
Instructions: Attach a rope or straight bar to a cable machine, stand facing the machine, grip the attachment with an overhand grip, and push the attachment down while keeping your upper arms stationary.

Name: Overhead Tricep Dip
Instructions: Lift a dumbbell over head, slowly extend it over and below your head, and lift it up again.

Name: Diamond Pushups
Instructions: Assume a push-up position, but place your hands close together, forming a diamond shape with your thumbs and index fingers, lower your body by bending your elbows, and then push back up to the starting position.

Name: Weighted Seated Dips
Instructions: Sit on a bench or chair, grasp the edge with your hands, lower your body by bending your elbows, and then push back up to the starting position while holding a plate on your lap.
